'''埃文·阿莫斯'''（{{lang|en|Evan Amos}}，{{bd|1983年}}）是高质量[[电子游戏机|电子游戏机]]图集[[摄影师|摄影师]]，并将自己的照片释出到[[公有领域|公有领域]]。他将自己的图片贡献到[[维基百科|维基百科]]，以及自由电子游戏数字档案馆“The Vamos Online Museum”<ref name="Destructiod">{{cite web|url=http://www.destructoid.com/evan-amos-is-gaming-s-most-popular-photographer-264824.phtml|title=Evan Amos is gaming's most popular photographer|publisher=''[[Destructoid|Destructoid]]''|last=North|first=Dale|date=2013-03-11|accessdate=2015-06-22|archive-date=2016-04-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160428154948/http://www.destructoid.com/evan-amos-is-gaming-s-most-popular-photographer-264824.phtml|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==生涯==

阿莫斯在对维基百科低质量游戏机图像表示“恼火”后，决定在“被时间遗忘”前记录这些系统。在2010年拍摄已有的[[Wii|Wii]]后，他很快“感到上瘾”，并开始登记所有他能想到的游戏机。在[[克雷格列表|克雷格列表]]发布广告后，他和纽约[[亨廷顿_(长岛)|亨廷顿]]一人联系，得以拍摄所有[[世嘉|世嘉]]主机和多款[[雅达利|雅达利]]主机。不久后照片逐渐流行让他“吃惊”，但他仍然很少署名<ref name="Gamasutra">{{cite web|url=http://gamasutra.com/blogs/EvanAmos/20131029/202882/The_power_of_Wikipedia_How_I_became_gamings_most_popular_and_anonymous_photographer.php|title=The power of Wikipedia: How I became gaming's most popular and anonymous photographer.|publisher=''[[Gamasutra|Gamasutra]]''|last=Amos|first=Evan|date=2013-10-29|accessdate=2015-06-22|archive-date=2020-11-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201124171441/https://gamasutra.com/blogs/EvanAmos/20131029/202882/The_power_of_Wikipedia_How_I_became_gamings_most_popular_and_anonymous_photographer.php|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Mashable">{{cite web|url=http://mashable.com/2013/11/10/gaming-photographer/|title=Introducing the Invisible Photographer Whose Photos Are Everywhere|publisher=''[[Mashable|Mashable]]''|last=Larson|first=Eric|date=2013-11-10|accessdate=2015-06-22|archive-date=2020-10-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201028064114/https://mashable.com/2013/11/10/gaming-photographer/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

阿莫斯表示了他的目的：{{quote|这有大量的需求。无人试图以此标准、以此质量、以此影响（维基百科）、以此形式（公有领域）提供此服务，确保照能从今延续几十年。我所创作的项目及其影响现已证明计划的重要性。这就是我创作并将之释放自由的原因<ref name="Gamasutra" />。}}

阿莫斯在2013年通过[[Kickstarter|Kickstarter]]集资1.7万美元，购买更多硬件、建立在线游戏硬件档案馆“The Vanamo Online Game Museum”，以记录电子游戏历史<ref name="Polygon">{{cite web|url=http://www.polygon.com/2013/10/31/5051928/preserving-video-game-history-one-photo-at-a-time|title=Preserving video game history one photo at a time|publisher=''[[Polygon_(website)|Polygon]]''|author=TraceyLien|date=2013-10-31|accessdate=2015-06-22|archive-date=2020-08-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200803092236/https://www.polygon.com/2013/10/31/5051928/preserving-video-game-history-one-photo-at-a-time|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Kickstarter">{{cite web|url=https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/1699256938/the-vanamo-online-game-museum|title=The Vanamo Online Game Museum Kickstarter campaign|publisher=[[Kickstarter|Kickstarter]]|accessdate=2015-06-22|archive-date=2020-11-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201126082903/https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/1699256938/the-vanamo-online-game-museum/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。Vanamo Online Game Museum除照片外，还有各游戏机的大量历史及开发事实<ref name="Gigaom">{{cite web|url=https://gigaom.com/2013/11/01/wikipedia-photographer-launches-kickstarter-campaign-for-an-online-video-game-museum/|title=See a Wikipedia photographer’s Kickstarter campaign for an online video game museum|publisher=''[[Gigaom|Gigaom]]''|last=Hockenson|first=Lauren|date=2013-11-01|accessdate=2015-06-22|archive-date=2020-10-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201030111623/https://gigaom.com/2013/11/01/wikipedia-photographer-launches-kickstarter-campaign-for-an-online-video-game-museum/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

阿莫斯在购买与拍摄主机后，将之捐献给纽约大学游戏中心和纽约国家欢乐博物馆，他若需要重射则可以随时前往<ref name="Mashable" />。

